<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Since when do melees always hit, and always hit for full?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
The DPS figures melee classes are fond of quoting always include misses and hits for low damage. The damage output does fluctuate a bit, but over time is remarkably constant. By contrast, mana classes are fond of quoting their <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  theorhetical</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> numbers (ie: 230 dps from sunstrike, which assumes zero fizzles and resists, and ignores the recast delay). All I am asking for is that we compare apples with apples where possible. Show me a log where a wizard does 13800 dmg in a minute (using sunstrike, and without crits, please) and I'll eat my shorts.<br>
<br>
Luxum wrote:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  However i'm still convinced that is the (admittedly unlikely) image of a team of wizards on full burn trivializing their pet high end encounters that causes VI to refuse to deal with our grouping problems. That's all i'm trying to say.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
This is a reasonable. I'll agree with your statement, though I stand by my assessment of the argument itself (now being attributed to VI) as being a poor one.<br>
<br>
Jonjay wrote:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> But that is as it should be IMO. Melee are a combination of cleric and melee.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
For conventional groups, the wizard is dependent on both the tank and the cleric to be able to do his damage. For AE groups, we need a healer as well (though you generally don't need a tank). To make the claim that melee damage must be somehow fractionalized when comparing it to wizard damage is not a fair and accurate comparison. Soloing is a different situation -- but when I want to play by myself I'll play Wizardry 8, thanks. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A> at: 2/6/02 12:50:46 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Moderator</font></td></tr></table><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Verant's #1 Fanboy</font></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 3245<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/6/02 2:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's depressing</span><hr size=1> First off, Glin, sorry to hear about your retirement.  I hope you'll reconsider after some time off, it would suck to lose ya man!<br>
<br>
Secondly...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Wizards have been broken for so long in standard single target groups it not even a joke any more.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Wizards, the class, the people, the ideas, whatever... are not broken!  I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> hate</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> it when people say this, it drives me crazy.  No, we're not broken at all.  We need some tuning in certain areas but we are absolutly not broken.<br>
<br>
People keep saying that SoL was just another melee spinner.  Guess what, you're not looking hard enough.  IMO this was a great expansion for casters.  Yes, there are new melee weapons and armor but why wouldn't there be?  There were new caster robes, spells, and weapons in SoV and that was a &quot;melee&quot; expansion.  <br>
<br>
What did we get in this expansion?  Let's see... FT stacking which was awesome.  TONS of new caster items that absolutly own.  Yes, believe it or not there are a TON of new caster items that blow stuff from high level SoV encounters away.  The INT/WIS softcaps were lifted partially and 200-255 INT/WIS raises our mana pool by a bit (approx. 319 extra mana at 60).  We also got a ton of new buffs to assist us in our endevors and expand our productivily.  <br>
<br>
Wizards (more than most other classes) also seem to be in the spotlight lately.  I've been asked to join random groups constantly and guess what, AE is the new thing that everyone wants.<br>
<br>
I was in a group yesterday in Plane of Growth.  It was composed of 2 very well equipped level 60 Warriors with SoDs, Primal, North stuff... a 60 Monk w/ some of the best equipment available to them, a 60 Cleric, a Level 60 Rogue w/ Myro Dagger etc, and of course me on a 60 Monk with some of the best equipment avail.  It was actually kinda funny, we were getting all of the experience... until two more guild Wizards showed up and grouped with a Rogue.  At that point we stopped getting EXP and the Monk in our group made a funny comment.  He said &quot;man, the Wizards are here... so much for getting EXP exclusivly.&quot;  Sure enough we didn't see much EXP after that reguardless of how hard we tried.  <br>
<br>
When we go to Ssra or Akheva the Wizards always form a group.  4 60 Wizards, 1 60 Mage, 1 60 Druid... other combos come around occasionally obviously, but for the most part this is pretty solid.  We always get the EXP because we're able to deal FAST HARD HITTING damage.  Yes, there is no argument from me that our long term damage dimishes but that's not our role.  In an EXP group I can contribute as much as a Rogue as long as I have c3 (or c2+gob) without the use of my Rend Robe.  <br>
<br>
Also, as a previous poster said, the new Luclin mobs have very high AC and a lot have curses which reduce attack or attack speed among other things.  This seriously hurts the melee classes.  9/10 named that we do have Wizard EXP written all over them. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Do I think we're perfect?  Nope.  Do I think we're broken?  Hell no.  Do I think we need work in some areas?  Yep.  Do I think we own in groups?  Kinda.  Do I think we suck in groups?  Absolutly not.  Do I think we need improvments in group desirabilty?  Yep.  <br>
<br>
Soloing - We rock.<br>
Raiding - We rock.<br>
Grouping - AE grouping we rock, normal grouping we're good.<br>
<br>
It's all about the midset you have really. <p><br>
