&quot;Wizards (more than most other classes) also seem to be in the spotlight lately. I've been asked to join random groups constantly and guess what, AE is the new thing that everyone wants.&quot;<br>
<br>
Rombus, I have to disagree. You guys really need to start qualifying statement, as this simply is not true for wizards below 50, and arguably below 56. Crits and AA are all really good things. But you have to remember that there is a substantial portion of Wizards who havent seen that stuff yet.<br>
<br>
I am level 51, and I can tell you SoL didnt change my wizard's life one iota. I do have more to look forward too now, I will grant you that. But don't pretend that is a watershed for wizards the realm over. <br>
<br>
Every wizard isn't like the wizards you guys hang around. Come back to the sub-50 game for a sec. Spend a few days in Paw, in Sol B or in Cazic, and talk to the wizards there. See how much the game changed for them. <br>
<br>
Every wizard isn't casting Sunstrike<br>
Every wizard isn't wielding an epic<br>
Every wizard isn't 55 with access to AA<br>
Every wizard isn't getting invites to AE groups<br>
<br>
I am very happy for wizards who DO fall into the above catagories. But you can't act like your experience is true for &quot;wizards&quot; as a whole. Avoid the generalities, they don't help any of us get any clearer.<br>
<br>
